The paper deals with multi-person pose estimation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed method involves correcting inappropriate labels using a teacher model, which is a machine learning approach and can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Part Affinity Fields (PAFs), which is a popular technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the performance improvement and speedup achieved through the proposed method, which can be related to neural networks (cs.NE) research.
